Act_report @WeRateDogs Data wrangling Project¶

This is a Notebook by Babatunde Akeredolu

This is a summary report of the analysis and visualizations of the Data Wrangling project of @WeRateDogs twitter archive. The insights from this project are:

  1. The most common dog stages are pupper, doggo and puppo
  2. The top three dogs with most average retweets are Stephan, Duddles and Jamesy
  3. The top three dogs with most average likes are Stephan, Jamesy and Duddles
  4. There is a linear relationship between no of retweets and no of likes.

Insight 4: There is a linear relationship between no of retweets and no of likes.¶

In [6]:
Image("image4.png")
Out[6]:

  • The chart above shows there is a linear relationship between the no of retweets in a post and the no of likes on the same post. This means that the more the retweets, the more the likes.

  • This supports our findings in the average retweets and likes charts as the dog with the most retweets are also the ones with the most likes.
